---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Knowledge sources" description="v2.0's plural-source knowledge discovery — docker-compose, kubernetes, env-registry, and custom plugins.">
  <h1>Knowledge sources</h1>
  <p>
    <code>substrate knowledge refresh</code> auto-discovers local-stack
    reference material (services, ports, env-var surface, secrets-by-key)
    and renders it into <code>auto/docs/KNOWLEDGE.md</code> — your
    canonical "what's running where" doc, redacted by default.
  </p>
  <p>
    v1.0 hardcoded docker-compose + <code>.env.example</code>. v2.0
    opens this up via a typed plugin contract under
    <code>substrate/knowledge-sources.yaml</code>:
  </p>

  <pre><code>sources:
  - kind: docker-compose
    path: ./docker-compose.yml
  - kind: kubernetes
    paths: ["k8s/**/*.yaml"]
  - kind: env-registry
    paths: [".env.production.template"]</code></pre>

  <h2>Built-in plugins</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Kind</th><th>Reads</th><th>Emits</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>docker-compose</code></td>
        <td>compose file</td>
        <td>service blocks (name, image, ports, depends-on, volumes)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>kubernetes</code></td>
        <td>k8s manifests (single + multi-doc YAML)</td>
        <td>Service / Deployment / StatefulSet / Secret / ConfigMap (keys only)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>env-registry</code></td>
        <td>env-var template files</td>
        <td>one block per key (values always redacted)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Glob support</h2>
  <p>Minimal expander suited to the common k8s + env-registry shapes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>**</code> matches zero or more intermediate directories. Skips <code>node_modules</code> and dotfile-prefixed dirs.</li>
    <li><code>*</code> matches one path segment.</li>
    <li>Literal segments match verbatim.</li>
    <li>Patterns starting with <code>.</code> discover dotfiles intentionally.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Custom plugins</h2>
  <p>
    Register your own plugin to surface internal-service registries,
    terraform state, or any other input shape. The contract is a pure
    function <code>(absolutePath, repoRoot, options?) =&gt;
    KnowledgeBlock[]</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code>import &#123;
  registerKnowledgePlugin,
  type KnowledgeBlock,
&#125; from "@op4z/substrate";

registerKnowledgePlugin("mycorp:internal-services", (path, root) =&gt; &#123;
  const data = JSON.parse(readFileSync(path, "utf8"));
  return data.services.map((s) =&gt; (&#123;
    sourceKind: "mycorp:internal-services",
    sourcePath: path.replace(root + "/", ""),
    category: "services",
    payload: &#123; name: s.name, image: null, ports: [String(s.port)] &#125;,
  &#125;));
&#125;);</code></pre>
  <p>
    Full contract in <code>docs/knowledge-sources.md</code>: naming
    conventions, block categories, determinism boundary, programmatic
    API, and the v1 → v2 migration steps.
  </p>

  <h2>Secret values</h2>
  <p>
    The kubernetes plugin reads <code>Secret</code> and
    <code>ConfigMap</code> resources but emits the <strong>key list
    only</strong>. Values never leave your repo's filesystem. The
    env-registry plugin similarly always redacts the placeholder
    value. Substrate's contract is "surface what's there"; never
    "exfiltrate what's there."
  </p>

  <h2>v1 fallback</h2>
  <p>
    Consumers without a <code>substrate/knowledge-sources.yaml</code>
    keep working — <code>substrate knowledge refresh</code> falls back
    to the v1 <code>substrate.config.json#knowledge.sources</code>
    flat-string list. Both paths render to the same
    <code>auto/docs/KNOWLEDGE.md</code>.
  </p>
</Base>
